CloudAccess Tools for EC2

To use the EC2 Command Line Tools: 
  Download the Command Line Tools from http://aws.amazon.com/developertools/351
  (For this example) Unpack the contents into ~/.ec2
  
  Set up your environment:
  # Thanks http://www.johnnypez.com/design-development/unable-to-find-a-java_home-at-on-mac-osx/
  export JAVA_HOME=/System/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/1.6.0.jdk/Contents/Home
  
  # http://docs.amazonwebservices.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/index.html?SettingUp_CommandLine.html
  export EC2_HOME=~/.ec2/ec2-api-tools-1.4.2.4
  export PATH=$PATH:$EC2_HOME/bin
  
  # AWS PEMs:
  export EC2_PRIVATE_KEY=~/.ec2/aws-my-pk.pem
  export EC2_CERT=~/.ec2/aws-my-cert.pem
  
  # ec2-describe-regions
  export EC2_URL=https://ec2.us-west-1.amazonaws.com
  
To use the CloudAccess Tools for EC2
  See the Examples  
